''' Define a variable and assign it a string "desserts" as a value. 
Then create three new variables, and assign them values by slicing the 
A) first 4 characters B) the last 4 characters and C) the entire string backwards as given values. '''

b = "desserts"
print(" The first 4 characters were:" + b [0:4])
print(" The last 4 characters were:" + b [4:8])
print(" The string backwards was:" + b [::-1])
